## Overview

Add `GET /api/relay/dead-letters/aggregated` endpoint that returns dead letters grouped by source + error reason, and `DELETE /api/relay/dead-letters` to clear dead letters matching a group.

## Files to Modify

- `apps/server/src/routes/relay.ts`

## Implementation

### GET /api/relay/dead-letters/aggregated

Add a new route that queries `relayCore.getDeadLetters()` and aggregates in-memory:

```typescript
router.get('/dead-letters/aggregated', async (_req, res) => {
  const deadLetters = await relayCore.getDeadLetters();

  const groups = new Map<string, {
    source: string;
    reason: string;
    count: number;
    firstSeen: string;
    lastSeen: string;
    sample: unknown;
  }>();

  for (const dl of deadLetters) {
    const key = `${dl.source ?? 'unknown'}::${dl.reason}`;
    const existing = groups.get(key);
    if (existing) {
      existing.count++;
      if (dl.failedAt < existing.firstSeen) existing.firstSeen = dl.failedAt;
      if (dl.failedAt > existing.lastSeen) existing.lastSeen = dl.failedAt;
    } else {
      groups.set(key, {
        source: dl.source ?? 'unknown',
        reason: dl.reason,
        count: 1,
        firstSeen: dl.failedAt,
        lastSeen: dl.failedAt,
        sample: dl.envelope,
      });
    }
  }

  return res.json({ groups: [...groups.values()] });
});
```

### DELETE /api/relay/dead-letters

Add a new route to clear dead letters matching a source + reason group:

```typescript
router.delete('/dead-letters', async (req, res) => {
  const { source, reason } = req.body as { source: string; reason: string };
  if (!source || !reason) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'source and reason are required' });
  }
  const deadLetters = await relayCore.getDeadLetters();
  const toRemove = deadLetters.filter(
    (dl) => (dl.source ?? 'unknown') === source && dl.reason === reason,
  );
  for (const dl of toRemove) {
    await relayCore.removeDeadLetter(dl.messageId);
  }
  return res.json({ removed: toRemove.length });
});
```

Note: Check the RelayCore API for the actual method to remove dead letters. If `removeDeadLetter` doesn't exist, check for `clearDeadLetters` or similar. The dead letter clearing may need to be implemented differently based on the actual API.

